The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for scene classification in remote sensing images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing datasets and proposes new directions for research, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multimedia data (cs.MM) in remote sensing images.
